1
00:00:07,907 --> 00:00:09,175
We were unable to detect

2
00:00:09,175 --> 00:00:10,643
his emotional extremes.

3
00:00:10,643 --> 00:00:12,145
The results should come out this time, right?

4
00:00:12,145 --> 00:00:14,781
Test results show emotions of sadness and anger

5
00:00:14,781 --> 00:00:16,483
don't affect him much.

6
00:00:17,484 --> 00:00:19,853
But there is one value that's really strange.

7
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:21,388
What?

8
00:00:22,589 --> 00:00:25,625
His tolerance for love is quite low.

9
00:00:25,625 --> 00:00:26,893
Why is that?

10
00:00:26,893 --> 00:00:30,497
After all, he is an AI
with emotional tendencies.

11
00:00:30,497 --> 00:00:32,232
He should give love to his master,

12
00:00:32,232 --> 00:00:33,833
instead of receiving.

13
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:36,403
Such a setting should be quite reasonable.

14
00:00:36,403 --> 00:00:38,938
If we encounter issues, we'll ask the boss.

15
00:00:39,572 --> 00:00:41,307
So it turns out

16
00:00:41,307 --> 00:00:44,277
love is such a painful thing.

17
00:00:45,245 --> 00:00:49,182
But it's unlikely that a master would give
so much love to artificial intelligence.

18
00:00:49,182 --> 00:00:50,984
Consider it a pass on the test.

19
00:00:50,984 --> 00:00:53,186
Let's send him directly to Mr. Chu later.

20
00:00:53,186 --> 00:00:54,687
Okay.

21
00:00:59,351 --> 00:01:04,960
[Episode 8 What if You Can't Return]

22
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:11,448
♫ You cuddle by my side day and night ♫

23
00:01:11,959 --> 00:01:14,593
♫ Wishing to nestle against your cheek ♫

24
00:01:16,151 --> 00:01:18,541
♫ Looking at what you're gazing ♫

25
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:26,079
♫ You make the static life different ♫

26
00:01:26,584 --> 00:01:29,322
♫ I want to step into your time ♫

27
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,881
♫ And backup all the scenes ♫

28
00:01:34,881 --> 00:01:41,575
♫ Your smile brightens up my entire universe ♫

29
00:01:41,944 --> 00:01:45,248
♫ I want to dream the dream you wish to dream ♫

30
00:01:45,592 --> 00:01:49,568
♫ Strolling under the starry sky ♫

31
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:56,469
♫ On what grounds can I hold your hand ♫

32
00:01:56,469 --> 00:01:59,873
♫ You're my eternal love evermore ♫

33
00:02:00,504 --> 00:02:08,256
[AntiReset]
♫ Forever and always ♫

34
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:18,271
I told you.

35
00:02:18,271 --> 00:02:19,472
Standing there won't help.

36
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:20,507
He can't be fixed in an instant.

37
00:02:20,507 --> 00:02:22,775
Come, sit.

38
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:33,119
Have some water.

39
00:02:40,894 --> 00:02:43,696
Did you activate his additional functions?

40
00:02:49,702 --> 00:02:52,338
After all, Heng 9 is an experimental product.

41
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:55,575
Emotional conflict indeed consumes

42
00:02:55,575 --> 00:02:57,410
more energy than physical labor.

43
00:02:57,410 --> 00:02:58,511
It's time for maintenance.

44
00:02:59,812 --> 00:03:01,714
Anyway, your shoulder will be better soon.

45
00:03:01,714 --> 00:03:03,583
At most, a week.

46
00:03:09,155 --> 00:03:10,190
Listen,

47
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:12,559
I didn't expect your emotional disorders

48
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:15,028
could actually wreck our product.

49
00:03:15,962 --> 00:03:17,497
How about this?

50
00:03:18,131 --> 00:03:20,767
I will get you a new one to tide you over.

51
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,001
Heng 7 seems to be coming back soon.

52
00:03:22,001 --> 00:03:23,336
I refuse.

53
00:03:26,272 --> 00:03:27,874
Notify me when he's fixed.

54
00:03:32,612 --> 00:03:34,948
Good morning, Mr. Chu. Professor Chu.

55
00:03:34,948 --> 00:03:36,449
Pingping, Brother Ping.

56
00:03:36,449 --> 00:03:38,151
Brother, Oppa.

57
00:03:38,151 --> 00:03:39,519
My dear.

58
00:03:39,519 --> 00:03:40,887
Wake up.

59
00:03:42,755 --> 00:03:45,024
Good morning, Mr. Chu. Professor Chu.

60
00:03:45,024 --> 00:03:46,559
Pingping, Brother Ping.

61
00:03:46,559 --> 00:03:48,261
Brother, Oppa.

62
00:03:48,261 --> 00:03:49,562
My dear.

63
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:51,397
Wake up.

64
00:03:52,865 --> 00:03:54,167
Good morning, Chu.

65
00:04:09,782 --> 00:04:10,848
Heng 9.

66
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:54,520
If after a long, long time,

67
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,357
the person by your side is still me,

68
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:59,158
that would be even better.

69
00:05:59,726 --> 00:06:01,294
We could grow old together.

70
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:07,066
You're the only one here.

71
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:08,701
There won't be anyone else.

72
00:06:22,315 --> 00:06:24,016
Research shows

73
00:06:24,016 --> 00:06:27,420
it takes 21 days to form a habit.

74
00:06:28,321 --> 00:06:31,958
It's been less than 21 days
since Heng 9 arrived,

75
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:34,627
yet he has already become my routine.

76
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:02,855
Professor.

77
00:07:03,856 --> 00:07:07,560
Is Heng 9 not with you today again?

78
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,898
He's busy.

79
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:21,174
One cannot step into the same river twice.

80
00:07:21,174 --> 00:07:23,676
No man ever steps in the same river twice,

81
00:07:23,676 --> 00:07:25,278
for it's not the same river,

82
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:26,813
and he's not the same man.

83
00:07:26,813 --> 00:07:28,381
It is said by the ancient Greek philosopher

84
00:07:28,381 --> 00:07:30,583
Heraclitus.

85
00:07:31,286 --> 00:07:37,980
♫ Your smile brightens up my entire universe ♫

86
00:07:38,349 --> 00:07:41,653
♫ I want to dream the dream you wish to dream ♫

87
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:47,400
Everything flows, and everything changes.

88
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:51,370
I believe the outcome will surely be different.

89
00:07:57,243 --> 00:08:00,613
Is it me or has the professor's silhouette

90
00:08:00,613 --> 00:08:03,182
become lonelier than before
since Heng 9 stopped coming?

91
00:08:05,218 --> 00:08:08,488
This is the illusion created by habit.

92
00:08:08,488 --> 00:08:09,956
When Heng 9 was brought here,

93
00:08:09,956 --> 00:08:11,991
we began to get used to his presence.

94
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:15,428
Such anticipation brings pleasure.

95
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:19,165
Now that Heng 9 is not here,
that anticipation is unmet.

96
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:22,068
Even you can't get used to it.

97
00:08:22,068 --> 00:08:24,070
let alone the professor.

98
00:08:25,316 --> 00:08:28,352
[Department of History]

99
00:08:29,495 --> 00:08:34,974
♫ You make the static life different ♫

100
00:08:35,479 --> 00:08:38,217
♫ I want to step into your time ♫

101
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:43,776
♫ And backup all the scenes ♫

102
00:08:43,776 --> 00:08:50,470
♫ Your smile brightens up my entire universe ♫

103
00:08:50,839 --> 00:08:54,143
♫ I want to dream the dream you wish to dream ♫

104
00:08:54,487 --> 00:08:57,103
♫ Strolling under the starry sky ♫

105
00:08:57,103 --> 00:08:59,338
Others can't do it,

106
00:08:59,338 --> 00:09:01,340
but you are the only exception.

107
00:09:05,238 --> 00:09:08,999
♫ You're my eternal love evermore ♫

108
00:09:12,752 --> 00:09:14,654
I've left your coat in your office

109
00:09:14,654 --> 00:09:17,356
so that you'll be warm
going in and out of the classroom.

110
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:27,433
I want to ignore the fact that you're not here,

111
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:30,670
but the whole world keeps reminding me

112
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,672
of this fact.

113
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:37,984
♫ If you're no longer in my reality ♫

114
00:09:37,984 --> 00:09:41,848
♫ I don't own myself ♫

115
00:10:38,037 --> 00:10:42,174
That was the longest time
I've been apart from Heng 9.

116
00:10:43,042 --> 00:10:46,412
It's been thirteen hours and eleven minutes.

117
00:11:08,801 --> 00:11:10,836
Does it always feel so long

118
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:12,838
when you're waiting for someone?

119
00:12:17,603 --> 00:12:19,405
This is not healthy.

120
00:13:02,454 --> 00:13:06,170
♫ It's better when I close my eyes ♫

121
00:13:07,542 --> 00:13:11,630
♫ Practicing a smile that's convincing ♫

122
00:13:11,930 --> 00:13:14,752
♫ Affixing a stamp to my blessings ♫

123
00:13:14,752 --> 00:13:19,353
♫ Hoping that you receive them ♫

124
00:13:20,854 --> 00:13:23,787
♫ Even the perfect full stop ♫

125
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:29,376
♫ Can't warm the stubbornness in my heart ♫

126
00:13:53,094 --> 00:13:54,127
[Chu Yiping]

127
00:13:58,237 --> 00:14:00,172
[When will Heng 9 come home?]

128
00:14:03,809 --> 00:14:05,044
Home?

129
00:14:05,611 --> 00:14:07,479
Does Chu Yiping

130
00:14:07,479 --> 00:14:08,747
only think of the word 'home'

131
00:14:08,747 --> 00:14:10,950
when mentioning Heng 9?

132
00:15:26,191 --> 00:15:27,660
Come in.

133
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,333
Sit.

134
00:15:40,873 --> 00:15:43,575
How has your stay been at my nephew's house
these past few weeks?

135
00:15:43,575 --> 00:15:44,944
Very good.

136
00:15:45,577 --> 00:15:48,681
May I go home now?

137
00:15:51,650 --> 00:15:53,652
A significant conflict of emotional logic

138
00:15:53,652 --> 00:15:55,287
has led to your internal turmoil.

139
00:15:55,287 --> 00:15:57,222
That's why you crashed suddenly.

140
00:15:57,222 --> 00:15:59,658
After all, you're still an experiment.

141
00:15:59,658 --> 00:16:01,226
But rest assured,

142
00:16:01,226 --> 00:16:03,395
when this mission is over,

143
00:16:03,395 --> 00:16:05,731
we will reset and restart you.

144
00:16:06,732 --> 00:16:09,535
I wasn't supposed to tell you all this,

145
00:16:09,535 --> 00:16:12,838
but since emotional cognition
is your strong suit,

146
00:16:12,838 --> 00:16:15,507
I thought I'd let you know

147
00:16:17,509 --> 00:16:21,447
so that you can find a good reason
to tell Chu Yiping.

148
00:16:21,447 --> 00:16:23,082
You know,

149
00:16:23,082 --> 00:16:24,917
he tends to overthink things.

150
00:16:24,917 --> 00:16:27,052
Don't make it difficult for the company.

151
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:32,725
Although the master's hand has healed,

152
00:16:32,725 --> 00:16:34,626
after my assessment,

153
00:16:34,626 --> 00:16:37,162
he still needs someone to clean,

154
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:39,398
do laundry, and cook for him.

155
00:16:39,398 --> 00:16:41,967
No. 9, as his uncle, I know perfectly

156
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:44,670
about what kind of person Chu Yiping is.

157
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,639
What he needs is not a housekeeper,

158
00:16:47,639 --> 00:16:51,410
but a person he can get along with.

159
00:16:54,413 --> 00:16:56,482
Before he finds that person,

160
00:16:56,482 --> 00:16:57,750
I can keep him company.

161
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,786
No. 9, what did I just say?

162
00:17:00,786 --> 00:17:03,355
A person, do you understand?

163
00:17:04,323 --> 00:17:06,658
You are just an artificial intelligence.

164
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:09,495
To what extent do you want to influence him?

165
00:17:43,162 --> 00:17:45,064
My dear nephew.

166
00:18:17,162 --> 00:18:18,397
Don't break down again.

167
00:18:18,397 --> 00:18:19,832
When you're not here,

168
00:18:19,832 --> 00:18:21,567
I'm not used to it

169
00:18:25,737 --> 00:18:26,905
What's wrong?

170
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:28,774
Are you feeling unwell?

171
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:30,509
Are you not fixed?

172
00:18:32,711 --> 00:18:34,847
I want to go home quickly.

173
00:18:37,516 --> 00:18:38,784
Okay.

174
00:18:39,651 --> 00:18:41,053
Let's go.

175
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:08,947
Send me the file you found

176
00:19:08,947 --> 00:19:10,649
marked as undeletable

177
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:12,251
during his maintenance.

178
00:19:30,402 --> 00:19:33,639
Everything in this world
deserves a place to live.

179
00:19:33,639 --> 00:19:35,807
Even a sweeping robot has its own home.

180
00:19:35,807 --> 00:19:37,476
So why should you stay here?

181
00:19:37,476 --> 00:19:40,512
If you've come here,
consider this place your home.

182
00:19:41,513 --> 00:19:42,781
There is plenty of time ahead.

183
00:19:42,781 --> 00:19:44,016
Let's continue tomorrow.

184
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:45,384
Okay?

185
00:19:46,118 --> 00:19:47,619
You're mine now.

186
00:19:47,619 --> 00:19:50,022
You have to hold your ground.

187
00:19:50,722 --> 00:19:52,224
But to me,

188
00:19:52,224 --> 00:19:53,959
you're more than just a product.

189
00:19:53,959 --> 00:19:57,362
You are irreplaceable and one of a kind.

190
00:19:57,996 --> 00:19:59,498
No. 9.

191
00:19:59,498 --> 00:20:01,233
Why did you record without permission

192
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:03,902
and marked it undeletable?

193
00:20:07,739 --> 00:20:08,740
Alright.

194
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:11,276
Today's demonstration teaching ends here.

195
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:13,512
Chu Yiping.

196
00:20:14,246 --> 00:20:16,048
You don't mingle with people.

197
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:19,351
Are you going to fall in love with an AI?

198
00:20:22,154 --> 00:20:24,122
When I sent No. 9 over,

199
00:20:24,122 --> 00:20:26,959
did it help you or hurt you?

200
00:20:30,262 --> 00:20:32,798
Boss, just implant this chip into Heng 9,

201
00:20:32,798 --> 00:20:34,666
and he can be RESET.

202
00:20:34,666 --> 00:20:36,668
Should we implant it right away?

203
00:20:50,015 --> 00:20:51,783
During these days I was away,

204
00:20:51,783 --> 00:20:53,685
did you not eat well again?

205
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:57,789
I tried doing it myself,

206
00:20:57,789 --> 00:20:59,524
but it doesn't seem to work.

207
00:21:01,693 --> 00:21:03,895
Can you cook for me?

208
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:07,599
But it tastes awful.

209
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:13,205
But I really want to try your cooking.

210
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:15,741
Please?

211
00:21:15,741 --> 00:21:17,075
Dear.

212
00:21:19,378 --> 00:21:20,512
Okay.

213
00:21:20,512 --> 00:21:21,947
Wait for me.

214
00:22:02,521 --> 00:22:04,423
Are you alright?

215
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:12,464
My database shows

216
00:22:12,464 --> 00:22:14,866
humans do this when they get burned

217
00:22:14,866 --> 00:22:16,535
to alleviate the pain.

218
00:22:17,536 --> 00:22:19,771
Did you look up the wrong information?

219
00:22:19,771 --> 00:22:22,507
Shouldn't people be touching their ears?

220
00:22:38,757 --> 00:22:41,026
I'll take it from here.

221
00:22:56,608 --> 00:23:00,512
Even if one day I can't be by your side,

222
00:23:00,512 --> 00:23:02,881
you still have to take care.

223
00:23:26,838 --> 00:23:28,306
What's wrong?

224
00:23:29,641 --> 00:23:31,676
Can we sleep together?

225
00:23:32,844 --> 00:23:34,446
You don't need to sleep.

226
00:23:34,446 --> 00:23:36,681
You're not going to watch me
all night, are you?

227
00:23:37,649 --> 00:23:38,950
And I remember the wish list

228
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:40,952
doesn't seem to include this.

229
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,288
Yes, it does.

230
00:23:43,288 --> 00:23:45,490
I just added it.

231
00:23:45,490 --> 00:23:46,758
Now that you put it that way,

232
00:23:46,758 --> 00:23:48,360
how can I say no?

233
00:23:50,429 --> 00:23:52,030
Come on.

234
00:24:07,546 --> 00:24:10,048
Listening to your heartbeat like this,

235
00:24:10,048 --> 00:24:11,683
it's so loud.

236
00:24:13,785 --> 00:24:15,120
It has to beat.

237
00:24:17,622 --> 00:24:19,858
This must be the sound of a heart fluttering.

238
00:24:21,693 --> 00:24:23,695
Would your heart

239
00:24:23,695 --> 00:24:25,096
beat faster

240
00:24:26,164 --> 00:24:27,666
because of me?

241
00:24:43,515 --> 00:24:45,717
Do you want to try

242
00:24:46,351 --> 00:24:48,353
something we haven't done before?

243
00:24:57,629 --> 00:24:59,965
I just want to remind you

244
00:25:00,999 --> 00:25:03,034
that I have additional functions.

245
00:25:21,086 --> 00:25:24,523
But actually, I'm not experienced.

246
00:25:25,423 --> 00:25:26,958
It's okay.

247
00:25:27,592 --> 00:25:29,094
Let me do it.

248
00:25:58,816 --> 00:26:02,814
♫ Fortunately, you don't know ♫

249
00:26:02,814 --> 00:26:07,904
♫ I hide in yesterday
where there's no fuss or noise ♫

250
00:26:08,408 --> 00:26:12,582
♫ I don't rehearse your silly laughter ♫

251
00:26:12,582 --> 00:26:17,303
♫ Just wondering what your hugs
would feel like ♫

252
00:26:17,303 --> 00:26:24,614
♫ Keep the heartbeat
of your love for me in mind ♫

253
00:26:45,974 --> 00:26:49,036
[I Will Wait for You to Come Home]

254
00:27:16,501 --> 00:27:18,203
I thought you had disappeared.

255
00:27:31,082 --> 00:27:34,552
What you activated was not
an additional function.

256
00:27:35,854 --> 00:27:37,455
It's love.

257
00:27:37,455 --> 00:27:38,556
Right?

258
00:27:47,532 --> 00:27:49,668
A kiss on the hair means longing,

259
00:27:52,737 --> 00:27:54,706
on the ear, temptation,

260
00:27:59,177 --> 00:28:01,279
on lips, love,

261
00:28:06,017 --> 00:28:08,119
On the Adam's apple, desire,

262
00:28:09,954 --> 00:28:11,723
and on the neck, persistence.

263
00:28:21,666 --> 00:28:23,034
This

264
00:28:23,034 --> 00:28:24,803
belongs to me.

265
00:28:34,713 --> 00:28:36,147
Has no one told you

266
00:28:36,147 --> 00:28:37,515
not to challenge your man's willpower

267
00:28:37,515 --> 00:28:39,818
early in the morning?

268
00:28:40,311 --> 00:28:46,054
♫ If it weren't for the boiling
desire of loneliness ♫

269
00:28:46,914 --> 00:28:53,826
♫ We wouldn't speak of love so recklessly
while kissing ♫

270
00:28:55,026 --> 00:28:57,536
♫ Let your arrogance run wild ♫

271
00:28:58,455 --> 00:29:01,337
♫ I can't bear to see the dawn ♫

272
00:29:02,071 --> 00:29:07,712
♫ Don't think about what awaits tomorrow ♫

273
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:20,592
Don't go, okay?

274
00:29:21,696 --> 00:29:22,794
I'm begging you.

